.TH "debug_register_mode" 9 "debug_register_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
debug_register_mode \- creates and initializes debug area.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "debug_info_t *" debug_register_mode
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "int pages_per_area "  ","
.BI "int nr_areas "  ","
.BI "int buf_size "  ","
.BI "umode_t mode "  ","
.BI "uid_t uid "  ","
.BI "gid_t gid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
Name of debug log (e.g. used for debugfs entry)
.IP "pages_per_area" 12
Number of pages, which will be allocated per area
.IP "nr_areas" 12
Number of debug areas
.IP "buf_size" 12
Size of data area in each debug entry
.IP "mode" 12
File mode for debugfs files. E.g. S_IRWXUGO
.IP "uid" 12
User ID for debugfs files. Currently only 0 is supported.
.IP "gid" 12
Group ID for debugfs files. Currently only 0 is supported.
.SH "RETURN"
- Handle for generated debug area
- NULL if register failed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates memory for a debug log.
Must not be called within an interrupt handler.
